author: Charlotte McCarthy
title: TV | Live Rugby World Cup 2015
text:
7.30pm - Pool B: New Zealand vs Georgia
By their own high standards, New Zealand's World Cup campaign got off to a rocky start when they were pushed to the wire by Argentina. They made up for that in their last game, smashing Namibia by 44 points, and it's unlikely that Georgia will provide much of a challenge. Watch out for all-black winger, Waisake Naholo, who is set to earn his second cap. The 24 year old cracked his fibula in July, but made an astounding recovery to be fit for the World Cup.
